College Cybersecurity Improvement Report
Objective

This report identifies key cybersecurity risks and recommends practical measures to improve the security of the college's digital infrastructure.

Top Five Risks
Unauthorized access to student information
Malware infections
Phishing attacks
Insider misuse
Weak authentication practices
Top Five Recommendations
Implement Multi-Factor Authentication
Provide regular cybersecurity awareness training
Update software and operating systems regularly
Maintain secure backups
Restrict access using role-based permissions
Expected Benefits
Improved protection of sensitive information
Reduced cybersecurity incidents
Faster recovery from attacks
Better compliance with security standards
Increased confidence among students and staff
Conclusion

By implementing these recommendations, the college can significantly strengthen its cybersecurity defenses and reduce the likelihood of future cyber incidents.